-create an ad or have an existing microsoft ad 
-create a windows server in ad region
-sysdm.cpl->to know ad domain
-ncpa.cpl->ethernet->rightclick->properties->IPV4->properties->advance->dns->add ip address of ad
-sysdm.cpl change the domain by entering your ad domain
-username-Admin
-go to server manager 
-click manage->add roles and feature->features->remoteserveradmintools->roleadmintools
-install & restart
-before logging into server, login with other account
-username-admin@domainname.com or onlydomainname/admin
-password-ur ad password
-dsa.msc->ad open
-click users of ur domain name and create users
-create sso and change identity to ad in settings, add users with permission sets
